# Abbreviations make code hard to read, and it has been
# suggested to throw them away altogether.  While an enticing
# idea, this is not practical IMHO.  What *is* practical is
# to limit their use to a list.  This list is for the
# current directory.
gc -- garbage collect
l_ -- at beginning, indicates a Lua wrapper
p_ -- at beginning, indicates a pointer
mt -- metatable
ud -- userdata
